{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-04714/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-04714"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:47:14"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["extreme close-up"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["exterior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["single shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A pair of hands digs up mushrooms."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04714/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-04714","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04714/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-04714"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04714/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04714/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04714/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04714/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04714/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04714/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04714/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04714/canvas/1/18f48799-c2df-4533-8310-daeb1ff71e65","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T18:55:27.270Z","creator":"Tallulah Stallvik","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>The moment of Alma removing the mushroom from the earth is shot in extreme close-up. This framing echoes the <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW113610947 BCX0\" href=\"https://digbmc.github.io/pt-annotated/items/phan-02442.html\"><u>many shots</u></a> of Reynolds at work on dresses. The film, then, presents two kinds of artistry. Reynolds’s aesthetics are rooted in creation and utilize fibers, while Alma’s is an aesthetics of destruction and based on the earth. The two use their creations (that is, dresses and poisoned omelets) to keep the other in check.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04714/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:409.7491229689807,267.7504154357459,944.1151218611523,643.1194608567209"}}}]}]}]}